snippet.textDisplay:
Wondering if Linus was feigning ignorance of Fahrenheit or not. amusing either way.

As much as I wish the entire world agreed on a single set of measurements, Im on the fence with Fahrenheit Vs Celsius. Fahrenheit is loosely based on how our bodies experience temperature, 90 being the early rough estimate of body temperature, and 0 being the freezing point of a brine solution. Given the US climate, many areas can reach both 100*F and 0*F, and we easily associate 0 with cold and 100 with hot weather that the US experiences. It's creation was crude but it made sense, and on the plus side, its more precise (given only integers) because there is less change in temperature per degree. I do agree that its easier to understand 0 is freezing and 100 is boiling. that's very straight forward and easy to use. So yea, hard to say what's better having known both.
